===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[universitas]]''', from '''[[universus]]''', "all turned into one", from '''[[uni-]]''', ''one'', + '''[[versus]]''', ''turned'', perfect passive participle of '''[[vertere]]''', ''[[turn]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/juːnɪˈvɜːsətiː/}}
* {{audio|en-us-university.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|universities}}

# Institution of [[high]]er [[education]] (typically accepting students from the age of about 17 or 18, depending on country, but in some cases able to take younger students in exceptional cases) where subjects are studied and researched in depth and degrees are offered.

